review_title: Your experience as Research Staff is completely dependent on your supervisor.
pros:
The benefits at UNL are generally very good.  Vacation and sick leave, affordable health coverage, matching retirement contributions, and casual atmosphere are all better than any place I've worked.  Your coworkers also tend to be better educated, and there is a collaborative spirit.

Added extras include being able to attend seminars in your area of interest by speakers from other departments, states, or even other countries.  Plus tuition is waived for the employee or designated family member.  Most supervisors encourage professional development, and participation in professional meetings.  And you can get a discounted city bus pass.

If you are in research, you have the benefit of being on the cutting edge.  You can feel like your work really contributes to your field.  There are also plenty of opportunities to exchange ideas or learn about something new that might give new insight to something you're working on.
cons:
Staff salaries tend to be very low.  After 7 years here my salary is still lower than the starting pay at my first job out of college (almost 15 years ago).  Generally speaking new hires will come in at the same salary as someone with a similar title who has been here for years.  It definitely takes a toll on the morale of longer term employees.

Your success and advancement are entirely at your supervisor's discretion.  Sometimes it is the luck of the draw- if you are lucky enough to be in a successful program or your supervisor gets a huge grant you might get a raise regardless of the quality of your work.  There is no consistency at the University or even Departmental level with regard to advancement.

Bad things happen here as in any large company.  I've seen bullying, gender bias, nepotism, truancy, harassment, and antics of the "old boy's club".  You can get away with a lot if you keep it subtle.
